## Public Static Functions

### additionalSizeToAlloc() {#a94ff4239f8807df0db66ade77e6b4f29}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename... Tys&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>static constexpr std::enable&#95;if&#95;t&lt; std::is&#95;same&#95;v&lt; Foo&lt; TrailingTys... &gt;, Foo&lt; Tys... &gt; &gt;, size&#95;t &gt; llvm::TrailingObjects&lt; BaseTy, TrailingTys &gt;::additionalSizeToAlloc (typename <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/trailing-objects-internal/extractsecondtype">trailing&#95;objects&#95;internal::ExtractSecondType</a>&lt; TrailingTys, size&#95;t &gt;::type... Counts)</>}
  labels = {["inline", "constexpr", "static"]}>
Returns the size of the trailing data, if an object were allocated with the given counts (The counts are in the same order as the template arguments).

This does not include the size of the base object. The template arguments must be the same as those used in the class; they are supplied here redundantly only so that it&#39;s clear what the counts are counting in callers.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/trailingobjects-h/#l00314">314</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/trailingobjects-h">TrailingObjects.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### totalSizeToAlloc() {#a5b733cf2a7d7206c2d2601cc5b024488}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename... Tys&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>static constexpr std::enable&#95;if&#95;t&lt; std::is&#95;same&#95;v&lt; Foo&lt; TrailingTys... &gt;, Foo&lt; Tys... &gt; &gt;, size&#95;t &gt; llvm::TrailingObjects&lt; BaseTy, TrailingTys &gt;::totalSizeToAlloc (typename <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/trailing-objects-internal/extractsecondtype">trailing&#95;objects&#95;internal::ExtractSecondType</a>&lt; TrailingTys, size&#95;t &gt;::type... Counts)</>}
  labels = {["inline", "constexpr", "static"]}>
Returns the total size of an object if it were allocated with the given trailing object counts.

This is the same as additionalSizeToAlloc, except it <em>does</em> include the size of the base object.
